{
  "stem": "25423.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were also those who where [NON-ENGLISH] men of the Gestapo.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 102,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Men who worked for the Gestapo, who were agents of the Gestapo.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 103,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, surely, and one of them, a prominent Jewish real estate operator here in New York, Bruce [NON-ENGLISH], was one of them.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 103,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What his role was I don't know, but I know that he was one of the movers and shakers in the Jewish community in the last Judenrats, which were essentially a mechanism to collect and destroy the community.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 104,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not in the beginning.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 104,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Eventually, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 105,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was there when the wall was erected, but I wasn't there when they closed because I didn't like to wait for that.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 106,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, they used, usually, the area.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 106,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "For example, there was a railroad track which separated the ghetto from the rest of the city, and the rest was fenced in.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 106,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Wooden planks--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 107,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 107,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Wire.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 108,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Barbed wire.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 108,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Pardon me?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 109,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Always.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 110,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were one or two entrances, simply because people used to march to work in the morning and come back in the evening.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 111,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Jewish police, sometimes Ukrainian police.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 111,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So, when you speak about the Jewish police, you see, it's very hard to say that they were all collaborators, and murderous, and henchmen.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 111,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Not necessarily.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 111,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's very fairly complicated subject.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 112,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Surely.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
